sequenceDiagram
    participant Browser as Browser / Client
    participant Server as HTTP Server
    participant Broker as SSE Broker
    participant HB as Heartbeat Loop
    participant Publisher as Event Publisher

    Note over Broker, HB: Broker created with NewBroker(config)
    Broker->>HB: Start heartbeat goroutine

    Browser->>Server: GET /events<br/>Accept: text/event-stream<br/>X-Client-ID: client-1<br/>Last-Event-ID: 42
    Server->>Broker: AddClient(w, r)

    alt Max clients reached
        Broker-->>Server: error: maximum client limit
        Server-->>Browser: HTTP 503 Service Unavailable
    else Streaming unsupported
        Broker-->>Server: error: streaming unsupported
        Server-->>Browser: HTTP 503 Service Unavailable
    else Success
        Broker->>Broker: Create Client{ID, Channel, LastEventID}
        Broker->>Broker: Register client in map
        Broker-->>Server: Set headers:<br/>Content-Type: text/event-stream<br/>Cache-Control: no-cache<br/>Connection: keep-alive<br/>X-Accel-Buffering: no
        Broker->>Broker: Start streaming goroutine
        Broker->>Broker: Start disconnect watcher goroutine
        Broker-->>Server: Return *Client
        Server-->>Browser: HTTP 200 (streaming)
    end

    Note over Browser, Publisher: Connection established, streaming active

    loop Heartbeat Interval (default 30s)
        HB->>Broker: Broadcast heartbeat Event
        Broker->>Broker: Format Event to SSE wire format
        Broker->>Browser: event: heartbeat\ndata: {"type":"heartbeat"}\n\n
    end

    Publisher->>Broker: Broadcast(&Event{ID:"43", Type:"update", Data:...})
    Broker->>Broker: event.Format() -> SSE wire bytes
    loop For each client
        alt Client buffer has space
            Broker->>Browser: id: 43\nevent: update\ndata: ...\n\n
        else Client buffer full
            Broker->>Broker: Skip client (non-blocking)
        end
    end

    Publisher->>Broker: SendTo("client-1", &Event{...})
    alt Client found and buffer has space
        Broker->>Browser: data: ...\n\n
        Broker-->>Publisher: nil
    else Client not found
        Broker-->>Publisher: error: client not found
    else Client buffer full
        Broker-->>Publisher: error: client channel full
    end

    Note over Browser: Browser disconnects or navigates away

    Browser->>Server: Connection closed
    Server->>Broker: r.Context().Done()
    Broker->>Broker: RemoveClient("client-1")
    Broker->>Broker: Close client channel
    Broker->>Broker: Delete from clients map
    Broker->>Broker: Decrement client count

    Note over Browser: Browser reconnects with Last-Event-ID

    Browser->>Server: GET /events<br/>Last-Event-ID: 43
    Server->>Broker: AddClient(w, r)
    Broker->>Broker: Create Client{LastEventID: "43"}

    Note over Broker: Application shutdown

    Publisher->>Broker: Close()
    Broker->>HB: Cancel context
    HB->>HB: Exit heartbeat loop
    Broker->>Broker: Wait for goroutines (WaitGroup)
    loop For each remaining client
        Broker->>Broker: Close client channel
        Broker->>Broker: Delete from map
    end
    Broker->>Broker: Reset client count to 0
